hopobject.body: When can you start? sirun erexaneri nkarner 2015 One solution to get around the restrictions is a partnership with a Chinese studio. But that leaves films at the mercy of the notoriously finicky Chinese censor. “How many successful co-productions have there been? It is difficult to think of many,” the executive says. One Hong Kong director, Gordon Chen, was blunt in his appraisal of whether Mr Wang, and China, could conquer the movie world. “What is the point of moving Hollywood to China? That is a lot of money,” he said, when asked about Mr Wang’s new studio.
